verbs.description: degarnish (third-person singular simple present degarnishes, present participle degarnishing, simple past and past participle degarnished)

entries.meaning: To strip or deprive entirely, as of furniture, ornaments, etc.; to disgarnish.
To deprive of a garrison, or of troops necessary for defence.
examples: to degarnish a city or fort
